Step 7: 

Sending Sensor Data to Blynk App
Now, we will:
✅ Read DHT11 (Temperature & Humidity), Rain Sensor, BMP180 (Pressure), and MQ-2 (Air Quality) values.
✅ Send these values to the Blynk App using ESP8266 Wi-Fi.
✅ Display the data in Blynk Widgets.

>>>Add the following widgets:
                               Value Display (For Temperature, Humidity, Pressure, Gas, and Rain Level)
                               LED Widget (For Rain Detection, optional)


>>>>>>>Assign Virtual Pins for each sensor:
V0 → Temperature
V1 → Humidity
V2 → Rain Level
V3 → Atmospheric Pressure
V4 → Air Quality (Gas Sensor)
